} Error message should be Your PR is eligible for sourcing approval. Please select one of the sourcing approvers and submit the PR again. Once the user selects the sourcing approver this should consider the workflow to move the PR to the selected sourcing approver. PR should be in sourcing review status after submission. The approverRef should accept the payload of the selected approvers. If the provided approver is not in the applicable list the API should return error that the selected approver cannot be applied. If the selected approver does not exist in Vroozi, it should give validation error that the provided approver does not exist.  {
    "id": "c8b1785c-ed91-447b-94f7-5112b7e7f69d",
    "status": "404",
    "title": "Not Found",
    "errors": [
        {
            "code": "404",
            "element": "approverRef.id", // "element": "approverRef.docNo" or "element": "approverRef.externalId",
            "message": "Field [approverRef.id] does not exist.",
            "detail": "Field [approverRef.id] does not exist. Provided value: [1709] does not exist.",
            "level": "Data Error"
        }
    ],
    "timestamp": "2024-02-21T10:40:31.859+0000"
} Once the PR is moved the sourcing approval, the approver should be able to approve/reject from email/UI. If the selected approver is not active in Vroozi, it should give validation error that the provided approver is not active. {
    "id": "c8b1785c-ed91-447b-94f7-5112b7e7f69d",
    "status": "400",
    "title": "Bad Request",
    "errors": [
        {
            "code": "400",
            "element": "approverRef.id", // "element": "approverRef.docNo" or "element": "approverRef.externalId",
            "message": "Provided approver is not active.",
            "detail": "Provided approver is not active. Provided value: [1709] does not exist.",
            "level": "Data Error"
        }
    ],
    "timestamp": "2024-02-21T10:40:31.859+0000"
} If there is no sourcing approval required the PR should be moved to financial or budget approvals depending on the workflow enabled. If the PR processing in external system toggle is enabled, the PR should move to submitted status after the Vroozi workflows are complete. PR should be visible and searchable in the approver UI screen. If sourcing review is enabled, it is automatically selected and PR will go to sourcing reviewer. Expose sourcingReviewerRef in the PR API. // We need to expose the approverRef in the PR as well Update public API documentation to reflect new fields. Update the confluence page to reflect the latest changes in the PR APIs. API Documentation updates: When a purchase request has only one eligible sourcing approver, the system automatically selects that sourcing approver. If multiple sourcing approvers are eligible to review or approve the purchase request, the user must select a valid sourcing reviewer or approver from the list generated by the system based on sourcing rules.
